727319f-a.title: Queens: Main Street - 39th Avenue
727319f-a.text:
Main Street, east side, north from 39th Avenue,showing
Flushing's main business Street. View 2 is north from near
38th Avenue.
P. L. Sperr  August 21, 1935
NO EPRODUCTIONS  Views 1,2

725291f-a.title: Queens: 39th Avenue - Main Street
725291f-a.text:
Thirty-ninth Ave., north side, just west of Main Street (right),
showing a rear view of St. George Chapel (former church) which faces on
Thirty-eighth Ave. This is an Episcopal church. Note the old cemetery.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

727333f-a.title: Queens: Main Street - 39th Avenue
727333f-a.text:
Main Street, west side, north from 4Oth Road, showing a continuation
in two views to Thirty-ainth Ave. lIn the foreground of view No. 1 is
the Vanderwater Grocery operated by John T. in the early 1870's. It was
later operated by Divine Vanderwater who sold to a Jamaica realty cor-
poration. In view No. 2 is seen the Geddes Paint store (half a century
here) and the Hepburn Pharmacy (established in 1870.) In the backmround
of view No. 1 is the steeple of St. George's Episcopal Church.
Aumust 1934.
View 2: 1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
